The government of the Switzerland through the Swiss Embassy has donated five portable isolation units to the Emergency Plus (E-Plus) Medical Services to boost the Covid-19 response. Emergency Plus Medical Services hosted Swiss Ambassador Valentin Zellweger during the handover of the portable isolation chambers. The event took place at E-Plus offices in South C, Nairobi. Present were E-Plus board chairman Dr Abbas Gullet and managing director Susan Ng’ong’a.